</gallery>

== Historic site ==
=== National Historic site ===
* '''Shimoikeyama Kofun''' (part of the "Yamato Kofun Group") – On October 6, 2014, the {{ill|Nomugi Kofun|ja|ノムギ古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nomugi Kofun|qq=}}, {{ill|Nakayama Otsuka Kofun|ja|中山大塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakayama Otsuka Kofun|qq=}}, and Shimoikeyama Kofun were collectively Historic site as the "Yamato Kofun Group."

=== Nara Prefecture Designated Historic site ===
* '''burial goods from Shimoikeyama Kofun''' (archaeological materials) – Preserved and displayed at the {{ill|Nara Prefectural Kashihara Archaeological Institute Museum|ja|奈良県立橿原考古学研究所附属博物館|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara Prefectural Kashihara Archaeological Institute Museum|qq=}}. Designated on March 31, 2006.

== Related Facilities ==
* {{ill|Nara Prefectural Kashihara Archaeological Institute Museum|ja|奈良県立橿原考古学研究所附属博物館|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara Prefectural Kashihara Archaeological Institute Museum|qq=}} (Kashihara City, Unebi Town) – Houses and displays burial goods from Shimoikeyama Kofun.

